  <source>Office of Rare Diseases (ORD)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      OBJECTIVES:

      Assess the safety and long-term efficacy of monoclonal factor IX concentrate in patients with
      factor IX deficiency.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      PROTOCOL OUTLINE:

      Patients receive monoclonal factor IX replacement therapy as inpatients. Patients with a
      satisfactory response receive further therapy as needed for bleeding for up to 36 months at
      home.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
